title: A1534 820-00244 no power
message:
Hi,
I have an A1534 820-00244 that has no power. I tried a new USB-C cable, but no success. The ampmeter stays black, and on F3050 I get 0V.
on F3050 i get 0.187V in diode mode.
Can you help?

title: A1534 820-00244 no power
message:
Check diode mode to ground at CC1/2 lines.
CD3215 is the first suspect here.

title: A1534 820-00244 no power
message:
USBC_XA_CC1 = 0.044V
USBC_XA_CC2 = 0.007V

It seams shorted.

Shall i replace CD3215?
